Jabari Bird (born July 3, 1994) is an American basketball player.

High school career[edit]

Bird played his high school basketball at Salesian High School where he led the Pride to an overall 100-8 record in his three years on the team.[1] Bird was a McDonald's All-American in high school and was the was the No. 20 overall recruit in the 2013 class.[2]

College career[edit]

As a senior at California, Bird averaged 14.3 points and 4.7 rebounds per game. He suffered a concussion in a loss to Oregon on March 11.[3]

Professional career[edit]

After finishing his senior year at California, Bird was selected with the 56th pick of the 2017 NBA Draft by the Boston Celtics.[4]
